    "However, 2D laser scanners can only perform plane scanning and generate low-resolution point cloud information, limiting its use for place recognition (Zhang and Ghosh 2000; Olson 2009; Zimmerman et al. 2023).",
    "The development of sensor technology has promoted point cloud sensing from 2D to 3D.",
    "Compared to 2D scans, 3D point clouds present more information for robots to better understand their surroundings.",
    "Therefore, 3D sensors have developed rapidly in the past three decades.",
    "3D point cloud data finds applications in many fields (Guo et al. 2020), including computer vision, autonomous driving, robotics, remote sensing, medical treatment, cultural relic reconstruction, etc."
